Release Notes:
==============
JSIDPlay2:
New Java requirements: (we are still Oracle-Java8 compatible) or as an alternative use OpenJDK 17 or newer (OpenJDK 11 is NOT supported)
New: aarch64 distributions added (e.g. for Apple M1), and as usual x86_64 releases
Bugfix: Prevent JSIDPlay2 to hang and scan whole directory tree, if called with a SID as command line argument
Bugfix: Thread safety issues fixed, when several recordings are done in parallel in the same Java virtual machine (e.g. recordingtool.sh)
Bugfix: automated tests repaired
Feature: Recording tool added for whole collections like HVSC using a configurable number of parallel threads
Feature: GMod2 cartridge support added (RAM expansion works fine, EEPROM functionality is untested)
Feature: Theater mode added to C64Jukebox (random HVSC playback)
Feature: Text2Speech added to JSIDPlay2Server calling external program espeak (https://espeak.sourceforge.net/)